<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A01</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Org should be hard-code in the initial release while the capability is not =
present.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
The capability is not currently supported by W1C.&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A02</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
All customer users are given the same entitlement in the initial release.</=
td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
The customer users will have a fixed set of access (client side library) un=
til the client library can fetch the entitlement dynamically.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A03</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
No parent child hierarchy will be implemented for the Beneficiary and accou=
nt.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Refer to the key decision part, the implementation will be a flat structure=
 based on Beneficiary. Beneficiary and account will have a 1:1 mapping and =
entitlement is on beneficiary id level.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
